The paper discusses a method for multi-agent learning, which is a topic that spans several sub-fields in computer science. The focus on reinforcement learning and the use of deep learning techniques suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses game theory and optimization, which are relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of generative adversarial networks and opponent modelling suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely category. Finally, the focus on multi-agent settings and the comparison with other multi-agent learning algorithms suggests cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) as a possible category.
